The winger has scored four goals in 21 appearances for the SPL side so far this season. 

Manager Jackie McNamara remains hopeful that Mackay-Steven will remain at the club, but his impressive form hasn't gone unnoticed.

The Scotland international has gone on the record in the past stating he has ambitions to play in the Premier League, but he may have to work his way up the leagues before realising that dream.

